physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Vaginal examination and pelvic ultrasonography revealed a cystic mass.
Repeated MR imaging revealed no increase in the size of the meningocele.
Total disappearance of the anterior sacral meningocele noted during postoperative rectal examination.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Postoperative course was uneventful for 1 week followed by wound swelling, cerebrospinal fluid leak, and meningitis.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Emergency reoperation revealed a purulent fluid leak and dehiscence of suture lines.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Repeated MR imaging demonstrated progressive decrease in the size of the meningocele until it completely disappeared.
